section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: However, it was reported in 2008 that the Foundation had a deficit of $200,000.
section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: After the singer went through conservatorship, her father and lawyer Andrew Wallet zeroed out the effort, leading to its closure in 2011.
section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: On October 30, 2001, Spears, alongside Bono and other popular recording artists under the name "Artists Against AIDS Worldwide", released an album consisting of multiple versions of Marvin Gaye's "What's Going On", with the intention to benefit AIDS programs in Africa and other impoverished regions.
section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: In the wake of Hurricane Katrina in 2005, Spears donated $350,000 to Music Rising.
section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: Later in 2011, the singer raised $200,000 during An Evening of Southern Style at a private residence in Beverly Hills to benefit the St. Bernard Project, with the help of several celebrities, including Hilary Duff, Selena Gomez, Kelly Osbourne, Kellan Lutz, and Kim Kardashian.

section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: Spears has also helped several charities during her career, including Madonna's Kabbalah-based Spirituality for Kids, cancer charity Gilda's Club Worldwide, Promises Foundation, and United Way, with the latter two focused on giving families from various disadvantaged situations new hope and stable foundations for the future.
section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: On October 24, 2015, Spears donated $120,000 to the Nevada Childhood Cancer Foundation.
section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: On October 27, 2016, Spears partnered with Zappos and XCYCLE to host the Britney Spears Piece of Me Charity Ride in Boca Park, Las Vegas to raise additional money toward her goal of $1 million for the NCCF, with $450,000 having already been raised from Spears's ticket sales and merchandise.
section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: The fundraising ultimately led to the development of the NCCF Britney Spears Campus in Las Vegas, which saw its grand opening on November 4, 2017.
section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: Spears also regularly participates in Spirit Day to combat bullying of LGBTQ youth and bullying.
section: == Other ventures == | === Philanthropy ===

sentences: In March 2020, Spears was participating in the #DoYourPartChallenge, which entails helping people with anything they might need during the coronavirus crisis.
